# SKILL: Carbon Market Domain Knowledge
*Portable context for AI agents working on carbon market tools.*
*Prevents re-explaining carbon market basics in every session.*

## Registry Types
| Registry | Type | Notes |
|----------|------|-------|
| Verra VCS | Voluntary | Largest voluntary registry. Projects get VCUs (Verified Carbon Units). OData API available. |
| Gold Standard | Voluntary | Premium voluntary credits. Focus on SDG co-benefits. |
| Puro.earth | Voluntary CDR | Carbon Dioxide Removal only. TSB (Tonne of Stored Biochar), CORC (Carbon Removal Certificate). API requires credentials. |
| Isometric | Voluntary CDR | New CDR registry. Rigorous methodology. API requires credentials. |
| MITECO | Compliance (Spain) | Spanish government registry. Type A (reforestation) and Type B (forest management). Submitted via OECC. |
| Alberta TIER | Compliance (Canada) | Technology Innovation and Emissions Reduction. |
| BC OBPS | Compliance (Canada) | Output-Based Pricing System, British Columbia. |
| CFR | Compliance (Canada) | Clean Fuel Regulation. |

## Credit Types
| Code | Full Name | Registry | Notes |
|------|-----------|----------|-------|
| VCU | Verified Carbon Unit | Verra VCS | 1 tCO2e per credit |
| CORC | Carbon Removal Certificate | Puro.earth | 1 tCO2e CDR |
| TSB | Tonne of Stored Biochar | Puro.earth | Biochar-specific CDR |
| CDR | Carbon Dioxide Removal | Generic | Category term |
| CORSIA | Carbon Offsetting and Reduction Scheme for International Aviation | ICAO | Aviation compliance |

## Key Methodology Codes (Verra)
| Code | Description |
|------|-------------|
| VM0047 | Afforestation, Reforestation, Revegetation |
| VM0044 | Improved Forest Management |
| VM0042 | Improved Agricultural Land Management |
| VM0048 | Reducing Emissions from Deforestation and Forest Degradation (REDD+) |
| VM0010 | Improved Forest Management |
| VM0026 | Sustainable Grassland Management |

## Methodology Groups (for aggregation)
REDD+, ARR (Afforestation/Reforestation), IFM (Improved Forest Management), Blue Carbon, Biochar, Landfill Gas, Methane, Renewables, Savanna/Grassland, Other

## Key Concepts
- **Vintage**: Year the carbon reduction/removal occurred. Buyers often specify vintage requirements.
- **Retirement**: When a credit is permanently removed from circulation (used for offsetting claim).
- **Issuance**: When registry issues credits to project developer.
- **Outstanding**: Issued but not yet retired.
- **Retirement rate**: retired/issued — measure of demand vs supply.
- **Buffer pool**: % of credits held back as insurance against project failure.
- **Additionality**: Would the emission reduction have happened without carbon finance?
- **Permanence**: How long is the carbon stored? Key risk for forestry projects.

