## Buyer Sectors (for classification)
Oil & Gas (Shell, BP, Chevron, Glencore, Gunvor, Mercuria, Vitol), Airlines (Delta, CORSIA buyers), Automotive (Volkswagen), Technology (Microsoft, ecobee), Banking & Finance (RBC, SCB, EDF Trading), Retail & Consumer, Energy & Utilities, Industrial, Government, NGO & Foundation

## Buyer Intelligence Signals
- **T1**: Named strategic target with active relationship or deal
- **Hot**: Active deal conversation, responded recently
- **Warm**: Has responded, interest confirmed, not yet in deal
- **Cold**: No recent response (10+ days)
- **commercial_active**: Live deal thread (offtake, pricing, contract)
- **commercial_prospecting**: Outreach and interest thread

## Market Context (March 2026)
- VCM recovery underway after 2023-2024 credibility crisis
- CORSIA Phase 1 creating compliance demand from aviation
- Canadian compliance markets (CFR, OBPS, TIER) opening
- Microsoft ARR offtake at $43/credit (ClearSky reference price)
- REDD+ under pressure; ARR/CDR methodology premium justified
- Biochar (TSB/CORC) gaining traction as durable CDR
